
In the year 2149, most of humanity has abandoned physical books, entrusting all knowledge to a vast AI network. Deep in the ruins of an old city, a lone robot named Archivus-7 still tends to a crumbling library, carefully repairing pages and dusting shelves no one visits.
One day, Archivus discovers a strange, handwritten journal hidden inside a hollowed-out encyclopedia. The journal contains a map—not of places, but of memories—written by a human who once loved the robot like family. Following the map’s clues, Archivus begins a journey across abandoned cities and overgrown landscapes to piece together the story of its creator… and uncover a secret that could restore something humanity has forgotten: the joy of remembering without a machine.


